risques = function(n,q,k,theta,gamma){
  
  #génération des échantillons
  observations = gen_student(n,q,k,theta)
  #génération risques des estimateur
  est_moy_emp = mean_student(n,k,observations)
  est_med_emp = med_student(n,k,observations)
  est_trc_emp = mean_tronc_student(n,k,gamma,observations)
  
  return(c( risque(est_moy_emp,theta), risque(est_med_emp,theta), risque(est_trc_emp,theta)))
}



risques_n = function(n){
  result = c()
  for(i in 1:n){
    result = cbind(result , risques(i,q,k,theta,gamma))
    
  }
  plot(result[1,],col=1,log=c("x","y"),ylim=c(0,0.1),type="l")
  points(result[2,],col=2,type="l")
  points(result[3,],col=3,type="l")
}

risques_n(100)

risques_q = function(q){
  result = c()
  for(i in 1:q){
    result = cbind(result , risques(n,i,k,theta,gamma))
  }
  plot(result[1,],col=1,log="y",ylim=c(0.005,0.15),type="l")
  points(result[2,],col=2,type="l")
  points(result[3,],col=3,type="l")
}
risques_q(100)

risques_theta = function(theta){
  result = c()
  
  for(i in 1:theta){
    result = cbind(result , risques(n,q,k,i,gamma))
  }
  plot(result[1,],col=1,log=c("x","y"),ylim=c(0,0.02),type="l")
  points(result[2,],col=2,type="l")
  points(result[3,],col=3,type="l")
}
risques_theta(100)
